    {
      "html": "The first two lines are deeply incised, the second two very lightly incised. Alpha has straight bar, with an apex; epsilon has equal length horizontals; mu in line 3 has extended apices, in anticipation of the cursive form; omicron is circular in lines 1 and 3, angular (made up of straight lines) in lines 3 and 4; sigma is and open four bar sigma in lines 1-2, a quadrate lunate sigma in lines 3-4; phi has a small elongated eye; omega is open in lines 1-2, lunate in line 4. It is therefore likely that lines 1-2 were incised by a different hand from lines 3-4."
